Kenny Baker (American performer) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenny_Baker_(American_performer) 0 Kenneth Laurence Baker (September 30, 1912 – August 10, 1985) was an American singer and actor who first gained notice as the featured singer on radio's The Jack Benny Program during the 1930s.
